<h2 id="other-characters" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#other-characters" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Other characters</h2>
<p>If you cannot find the character you're looking for in the table above, please look at this full list of <a href="https://github.com/ehmicky/cross-platform-terminal-characters" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">cross-platform terminal characters<ExternalLinkIcon/></a>.</p>
<h2 id="unsupported-terminals" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#unsupported-terminals" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Unsupported terminals</h2>
<p>The following terminals are not officially supported:</p>
<ul>
<li>xterm</li>
<li>Linux Terminal (kernel)</li>
<li>cmder</li>
</ul>
<p>They can display most but not all of the symbols listed above.</p>
